Three American brothers who have not spoken to each other in a year set off on a 
train voyage across India with a plan to find themselves and bond with each 
other -- to become brothers again like they used to be. Their "spiritual quest", 
however, veers rapidly off-course (due to events involving over-the-counter pain 
killers, Indian cough syrup, and pepper spray), and they eventually find 
themselves stranded alone in the middle of the desert with eleven suitcases, a 
printer, and a laminating machine. At this moment, a new, unplanned journey 
suddenly begins.
